2nd Reason: From the Rule that in doubtful matters we must choose the safe side. It is safer to obey than to disobey with a doubtful conscience3 for it is safer to err in exoess of honour to superiors than in defect.

3rd Reason: From the same Rule3 It is safer to believe ourselves obliged when we are really free, than to believe ourselves free when we are really obliged. For we oftener err from overboldness than from fear3 from impatience of constraint than from patience. Hence we must make it our habitual maxim, that laws not obviously unJust, are to be obeyed, in order to check such propensities.
